I"â<p>Unapologetics: a play on the word <em>unapologetic</em>, meaning put forth without qualification, and the word <em>apologetics</em>, based on the Greek <em>apologia</em>, meaning a systematic argumentative discourse in defense of an idea.</p>

<p><br /></p>

<p>I affirm, not as a means of opinion, that Christ is supreme, in all things, at all times, in all endeavors, and in all places, and that every single person on earth is born openly rebelling against His supremacy.</p>
